function reverse(str) {
    for (var i=str.length-1;i>-1;--i) {
        if (str[i] === "(") {
            var close = findClose(str, i + 1);
            if (close < 0 || i >= close) {
                throw "Unexpected close for open at " + i;
            }
            
            str = str.flip(i + 1, close - 1);
            str = str.removeAt(close, 1);

    Matcher m = Pattern.compile("\\(\\w+\\)").matcher(s);
    m.find();
    String ms = m.group();
    new StringBuffer(ms).reverse().getChars(1, ms.length(), sc, m.start());
    s = new String(sc).replaceAll("\\(\\)", "");
    if (s.contains("("))
        s = reverse(s);
    return s;
